title: Lake Geneva Wisconsin and White River Holdings

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Wisconsin Open Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Pursuant to the Wisconsin Public Records Law (Wis. Stat. §§ 19.31–19.39), I am requesting copies of all emails, notes, and correspondence between the City of Lake Geneva (including staff, elected officials, and any agents or representatives of the City) and White River Holdings LLC concerning the deed restriction on the following properties:

Tax Key No. ZOP 0001

Tax Key No. ZYUP 00131

Tax Key No. ZYUP 00001A

Tax Key No. ZYUP 00001C

Parcel .3 — Tax Key No. ZYUP 00153

This request specifically includes, but is not limited to, communications relating to the Special Warranty Deed dated December 9, 2022 and any subsequent discussions, negotiations, or modifications related to that deed restriction.

If any records are withheld in whole or in part, please provide the specific statutory exemption relied upon and describe the nature of the records being withheld.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Gary Milliette

To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Mississippi Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Regarding the former Columbus PD Officer Robin Conner, 33, incident that occurred on 02/21/2024, just after 12 p.m. at (Dick’s Sporting Goods) 2041 US-45 N, Columbus, MS 39705. Gray was arrested on the charges of shoplifting.
Specifically, I am seeking to obtain electronic copies of the:
1. BWC footage recorded by the arresting Officer and assisting Officers detailing their full involvement in this incident. 
2. Incident report.
To assist you in locating the footage here are the key details of the incident:
   
Date of Event: 02/21/2024
Names: Robin Conner
Location of Event: (Dick’s Sporting Goods) 2041 US-45 N, Columbus, MS 39705 
Please let me know if you require further information to process it.
If any aspects of this request are denied, please cite each specific exemption you feel justifies the refusal to release the information and please notify me of the appeal procedures available to me under the law.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 7 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Marius Christensen

title: City of Lake Geneva Wisconsin owned property appraisals

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Wisconsin Open Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Pursuant to the Wisconsin Public Records Law (Wis. Stat. §§ 19.31–19.39), I am requesting copies of any and all appraisals, valuations, or opinions of value prepared for or provided to the City of Lake Geneva for the city-owned property known as Hillmoor, which abuts Highway 50 in Lake Geneva, Wisconsin.

This request includes, but is not limited to, all formal written appraisals, market analyses, broker price opinions, or any other valuation documents in the City’s possession, whether prepared internally or by outside parties, regardless of date.

title: Documents related to 6651 E Vernor - Planning and Development

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Michigan Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Any and all of the following documents, from January 1, 2010 to August 4, 2024 related to the property with the parcel ID: 15011719 or address 6651 East Vernor Highway: 
1. Emails and other correspondence, including attachments, between agency staff and Patrick McCabe and/or his representatives regarding the sale of this parcel.
2. Proposals for use of lot including schedule, architectural renderings
3. Terms of sale, including use, timeline and scheduled check-ins

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Tracie McMillan
